# Definition of Done

Always follow [`docs/standards/definition-of-done.md`](docs/standards/definition-of-done.md).

Before describing repository work as complete, and before preparing a commit:

1. Run a Definition of Done review against every applicable section.
2. Perform and report a Documentation Impact Review (or state `Documentation impact: None` with a brief reason).
3. Report verification that was actually run. Do not claim unrun checks passed.
4. If an applicable requirement is incomplete, identify it explicitly instead of declaring the work complete.

Do not commit or push unless the user explicitly requests it.
